SIMPLE: chalybeate
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Chalybeate
<hw>Cha*lyb"e*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[NL.
<ets>chalybeatus</ets>, fr. <ets>chalube⟦ium⟧us</ets>. See
<er>Chalubean</er>.]</ety> <def>Impregnated with salts of iron; having a
taste like iron; <as>as, <ex>chalybeate</ex> springs</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chalybeate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Chalybeate
<hw>Cha*lyb"e*ate</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Any water, liquid, or
medicine, into which iron enters as an ingredient.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chalybeous</ent>⟦br⟧
